#This is a sample file distributed with Galaxy that enables tools
#to use the ml_models model folder. The ml_models.loc
#file needs this format (white space is the TAB character):

#<type-model_id-variant-version>	<model_family>	<variant>	<version>	<display_name>	<sort_key>  <model_type>    <compatibility> <path>  <doi>	<license> <creators>

# for example:
ocr-catmus_print-tiny-v1    CATMuS-Print	tiny	v1	CATMuS-Print [Tiny] CATMuS-Print__020   ocr kraken /db/models/kraken_ocr/2026-07/ocr/catmus-print-fondue-tiny.mlmodel	10.5281/zenodo.10602357   CC-BY-4.0   Simon Gabay
ocr-catmus_print-large-v1	CATMuS-Print	large	v1	CATMuS-Print [Large]    CATMuS-Print__010   ocr kraken  /db/models/kraken_ocr/2026-07/ocr/catmus-print-fondue-large.mlmodel	CATMuS-Print__010   10.5281/zenodo.10592716 CC-BY-4.0   Simon Gabay
seg-bdd-regions-default-v1	BDD-Segmentation-Regions	default	v1	BDD-Segmentation-Data   BDD-Segmentation-Data__010  segmentation    kraken	/db/models/kraken_ocr/2026-07/segmentation/bdd-segmentation-regions-1.0.mlmodel	10.5281/zenodo.10890966 CC-BY-4.0   Michael Schonhardt